             Copper fell for the first time in
four days after U.S. service industries expanded at a slower
pace than forecast, adding to investorsâ€™ concerns that the
global economic recovery may weaken.  
 Market News:  
 Metals News:  
 Metal Prices:  

 
-- Copper fell 1.2 percent at $6,528 a metric ton on the London
Metal Exchange at 7:30 a.m. Relative Strength Index 47.6.
-- Aluminum dropped 1.1 percent to $1,973 a ton. RSI 48.7.
-- Zinc declined 1.2 percent at $1,828 a ton. RSI 49.5.
-- Lead lost 1.2 percent at $1,759 a ton. RSI 47.
-- Nickel was unchanged at $18,900 a ton. RSI 42.6.
-- Tin retreated 0.9 percent at $17,450 a ton. RSI 49.3.

